OK, I got it working.  

Ewout&#39;s .kmn file is apparently empty.  I have written a slightly 
different experimental version of a .kmn file which I am playing 
with.  It helps me to type the right Shavian and Quickscript 
characters.  It works with all shavian and quickscript fonts and 
meets the need for a chording keyboard I mentioned earlier.  

I expect I will be changing it some as time goes on, but wanted to 
offer it as a possible beginning point if you are playing with the 
keyboard stuff.  

The mapping is as follows:

&quot;s&quot; + &quot;h&quot;  &gt; &quot;S&quot;
